{
  "texts": [
    "The left plot presents trends over time in the NLP field, showing the percentages of papers for each mechanism, as predicted by an LLM.",
    "The right plot presents pie charts with the percentage distribution of the mechanisms: the inner pie shows the distribution within the NLP field, and the outer pie shows for fields outside of NLP.",
    "NLP community are generally stable over time.",
    "However, two leading paradigms, Feature Attributions and Natural Language Explanations, demonstrate contrasting trends: the proportion of Feature Attribution papers has gradually decreased (from ~45% in 2017 to ~30% in 2024) while papers on Natural Language Explanations have increased (from ~10% in 2017 to ~25% in 2024).",
    "The latter rise is likely attributed to advancements in text generation capabilities, which will be discussed later."
  ]
}